b'[<p><i><b>UFC 142: Aldo vs. Mendes</b></i> was a <a href="/wiki/Mixed_martial_arts" title="Mixed martial arts">mixed martial arts</a> event held by the <a href="/wiki/Ultimate_Fighting_Championship" title="Ultimate Fighting Championship">Ultimate Fighting Championship</a> on January 14, 2012 at the <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/HSBC_Arena_(Rio_de_Janeiro)" title="HSBC Arena (Rio de Janeiro)">HSBC Arena</a> in <a href="/wiki/Rio_de_Janeiro" title="Rio de Janeiro">Rio de Janeiro</a>, <a href="/wiki/Brazil" title="Brazil">Brazil</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-UFC_142_3-0"><a href="#cite_note-UFC_142-3">[3]</a></sup> It was the first UFC event of the year, and was broadcast live on <a href="/wiki/Pay-per-view" title="Pay-per-view">pay-per-view</a> in <a href="/wiki/North_America" title="North America">North America</a>.\n</p>, <p><i>UFC 142</i> featured preliminary fights live on <a href="/wiki/Sportsnet" title="Sportsnet">Sportsnet</a> and <a href="/wiki/FX_(TV_channel)" title="FX (TV channel)">FX</a>.\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Siyar_Bahadurzada" title="Siyar Bahadurzada">Siyar Bahadurzada</a> was scheduled to face <a href="/wiki/Erick_Silva" title="Erick Silva">Erick Silva</a>, but pulled out of the bout.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-mass_casualties_4-0"><a href="#cite_note-mass_casualties-4">[4]</a></sup> Veteran fighter <a href="/wiki/Carlo_Prater" title="Carlo Prater">Carlo Prater</a> stepped in as a replacement for Bahadurzada.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-PraterIn_5-0"><a href="#cite_note-PraterIn-5">[5]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Rob_Broughton" title="Rob Broughton">Rob Broughton</a> was scheduled to face Ednaldo Oliveira, but pulled out of the bout.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-mass_casualties_4-1"><a href="#cite_note-mass_casualties-4">[4]</a></sup> Recently resigned heavyweight <a href="/wiki/Gabriel_Gonzaga" title="Gabriel Gonzaga">Gabriel Gonzaga</a> replaced Broughton in the bout.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-GonzagaIn_6-0"><a href="#cite_note-GonzagaIn-6">[6]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Paulo_Thiago" title="Paulo Thiago">Paulo Thiago</a> was scheduled to face <a href="/wiki/Mike_Pyle_(fighter)" title="Mike Pyle (fighter)">Mike Pyle</a>, but pulled out of the bout due to an injury.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-mass_casualties_4-2"><a href="#cite_note-mass_casualties-4">[4]</a></sup> Recently resigned welterweight <a href="/wiki/Ricardo_Funch" title="Ricardo Funch">Ricardo Funch</a> replaced Thiago in the bout.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-FunchIn_7-0"><a href="#cite_note-FunchIn-7">[7]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Stanislav_Nedkov" title="Stanislav Nedkov">Stanislav Nedkov</a> was scheduled to take on <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Fabio_Maldonado" title="Fabio Maldonado">Fabio Maldonado</a> at this event, but visa problems forced Nedkov to withdraw from the bout.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-mass_casualties_4-3"><a href="#cite_note-mass_casualties-4">[4]</a></sup> Newcomer <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Caio_Magalhaes" title="Caio Magalhaes">Caio Magalhaes</a> stepped in as a replacement for Nedkov in late December.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-MagalhaesIn_8-0"><a href="#cite_note-MagalhaesIn-8">[8]</a></sup> However, Maldonado was injured less than a week before his fight with Magalhaes and the bout was scratched from the card.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-MaldonadoMagalhaesScratch_9-0"><a href="#cite_note-MaldonadoMagalhaesScratch-9">[9]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>At the UFC 142 weigh ins, <a href="/wiki/Anthony_Johnson_(fighter)" title="Anthony Johnson (fighter)">Anthony Johnson</a> failed to make the middleweight limit. Johnson came in 11 pounds over the 186 lb weight allowance, was fined 20 percent of his earnings and the bout was contested at a catchweight of 197 lb.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-weight_10-0"><a href="#cite_note-weight-10">[10]</a></sup> However, Belfort requested that Johnson not weigh more than 205 lb the day of the fight. The UFC mandated that if Johnson could not make the 205 lb limit, the bout would be cancelled. Johnson officially weighed in at 204.2 lb on fight day, and the bout took place as scheduled.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-11"><a href="#cite_note-11">[11]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>Fighters were awarded $65,000 bonuses.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-16"><a href="#cite_note-16">[12]</a></sup>\n</p>]'